summary: An ordinance licensing and regulating the business of peddling and hawking and the conduct of persons engaged therein in the City of Seattle, providing penalties for violation thereof and repealing Sections 49, 50, 51, 52, 53, 54, and 55 of Ordinance No. 15855, entitled: "An ordinance to license and regulate certain trades and occupations in the City of Seattle and providing penalties for the violation thereof" approved April 25, 1907.
